\chapter{SYSTEM DESIGN}

\section{System Architecture}
The Food Allergy Risk Estimation System follows a layered architecture consisting of presentation, application, intelligent, and data layers. The presentation layer provides a user-friendly interface for uploading food images and entering allergy details using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

The application layer, implemented using Python Flask, handles user requests, performs image preprocessing, and manages the overall system workflow. The intelligent layer performs the core analysis, where the MobileNetV2 model identifies the food item, and rule-based logic estimates ingredients, matches them with user allergies, and determines the risk level as Low, Medium, or High.

The data layer stores user allergy profiles and food-related data using JSON. This layered approach ensures efficient processing, modular design, and easy system maintenance.

