The \texttt{preprocess\_image} function prepares the input image for the machine learning model. It converts the image to RGB format, resizes it to 224×224 pixels, and normalizes pixel values to a range of 0 to 1. The image is then converted into a numerical array and reshaped into a batch format suitable for the MobileNetV2 model. The processed image is returned for further classification.
