\chapter{CONCLUSION}
The Food Allergy Risk Estimation System is developed as a practical solution to address the challenges faced by individuals with food allergies, especially in situations where ingredient information is not readily available. The system combines machine learning and rule-based logic to analyze food images, identify the dish, estimate possible ingredients, and evaluate potential allergy risks based on user-specific preferences.

The implementation of the MobileNetV2 model enables efficient food classification with an accuracy of 79\%, while maintaining low computational requirements. The use of a custom-built dataset improves the relevance of predictions for real-world food items. Additionally, the integration of ingredient estimation and allergy matching enhances the system’s ability to provide meaningful and personalized risk assessments.

The system provides outputs in a clear and understandable format, including food identification, confidence score, and allergy risk level, which helps users make informed decisions before consuming food. Although the system does not guarantee complete accuracy, it serves as an effective decision-support tool that raises awareness about potential food allergens and reduces the chances of accidental exposure.

Overall, the project demonstrates the effective application of image processing, machine learning, and intelligent system design in solving a real-world problem. It highlights the importance of combining AI techniques with practical logic to create user-friendly and impactful solutions.

\section{Future Scope}
While the system achieves its primary objectives, there are several opportunities for further enhancement and development:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Dataset Expansion:} Increasing the size and diversity of the custom dataset to improve model accuracy and generalization across various food categories.
    \item \textbf{Advanced Model Integration:} Incorporating more powerful deep learning models such as EfficientNet or ResNet to enhance food classification performance.
    \item \textbf{Real-Time Food Detection:} Implementing live camera-based scanning for instant food recognition and allergy risk estimation.
    \item \textbf{Improved Ingredient Prediction:} Developing multi-label classification techniques to identify multiple ingredients more accurately.
    \item \textbf{Mobile Application Development:} Creating a dedicated mobile application to improve accessibility and user experience.
    \item \textbf{Cloud-Based Integration:} Integrating cloud storage and APIs for scalable data management and faster processing.
    \item \textbf{Cuisine and Region-Based Ingredient Mapping:} Enhancing ingredient estimation by incorporating cuisine and regional variations to improve the accuracy of inferred ingredients.
    \item \textbf{Enhanced User Interaction:} Extending the system to provide detailed nutritional information along with allergen detection.
    \item \textbf{Robustness Improvement:} Enhancing system performance for complex dishes, mixed foods, and low-quality images.
\end{itemize}

